Elwood Bredell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elwood_Bredell 0 Elwood Bailey Bredell (6 August 1884 – 22 May 1976) was an English cinematographer and occasional actor. Bredell worked on such films as The Killers (1946), The Unsuspected (1947) and the 1955 B-movie Female Jungle. He is sometimes credited as Woody Bredell or Elwood Burdell.
